# n8n Reuse First

Before creating a new component or composable, search for an existing equivalent. Custom UI introduced where a primitive exists is the largest source of duplicated work and visual drift in this codebase.

## Search order

1. `packages/frontend/@n8n/design-system/src/components/` — primitives (`N8nButton`, `N8nCard`, `N8nIconButton`, `N8nSelect`, `N8nDateRangePicker`, `N8nInput`, `N8nMarkdown`, etc.). Avoid components marked `@deprecated`.
2. Feature-local equivalents in the area you're working on:
   - Insights: `InsightsSummary`, `InsightsChart*`, `InsightsDataRangePicker`, `transformInsightsSummary`, `transformInsightsTimeSaved`, `formatInsightsTimeSavedLabel`.
   - Chat surfaces: `ChatInputBase`, `ChatMarkdownChunk`, `ChatTypingIndicator`, the prompt-suggestion mixin in `_prompt-suggestion-buttons.scss`.
   - AI assistant: `InstanceAi*` and `Agent*` already cover most chat patterns.
3. Shared composables under `packages/frontend/editor-ui/src/app/composables/` and feature-local stores.

## When you must create something new

- Document the search in the PR description (which existing components you considered, why none fit). Future reviewers will check.
- Place pure UI primitives in `@n8n/design-system`, not in editor-ui.
- Place feature-specific composition in the feature folder, not under `app/`.
- Use semantic tokens only. No hardcoded `px`/`rem`. No `_tokens.legacy.scss` imports.

## Concrete recent examples

- The Insights Analyst dashboard reuses `InsightsSummary` with the new `linkVariant="static"` prop instead of duplicating the KPI strip styling.
- The Insights Analyst chat panel reuses `ChatInputBase` (sticky input + send/stop) and `ChatTypingIndicator` (three blinking dots) instead of recreating both.
- Time-saved labels go through `formatInsightsTimeSavedLabel(minutes)` which centralizes the i18n + minute/hour switch.
